<p>Irena's Vow</h1></p>

<p>From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</p>


<ref class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</ref>
<ref class="mw-jump-link" href="#p-search">Jump to search</ref>
<p>Irena's Vow is a <ref target="/wiki/Broadway_theatre" title="Broadway theatre">Broadway</ref> play recounting the story of <ref class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Irena_Gut" title="Irena Gut">Irena Gut</ref>, a Polish nurse who, at the risk of her life, saved twelve <ref class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Jew" title="Jew">Jews</ref> during <ref target="/wiki/World_War_II" title="World War II">World War II</ref> in <ref target="/wiki/Nazi_Germany" title="Nazi Germany">German</ref>-<ref class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Occupied_Poland" title="Occupied Poland">occupied Poland</ref>.<ref target="#cite_note-playbill-1">[1]</ref></p>

